definitions: Happening or arising without apparent external cause; self-generated.
Arising from a natural inclination or impulse and not from forethought or prompting.
Unconstrained and unstudied in manner or behavior.
Marked by or having a disposition to talk.
Inclined to talk or converse; ready or apt to engage in conversation; freely communicative; chatty.
Being reserved.
Showing nervousness timidity in the company of other people.
To continue or persist in doing, believing, or using something.
To remain loyal to, committed to, or supportive of something.
Characterized by or having good sense or compassion.
Approving [An understanding person who has the ability to know how other people are feeling, and can forgive them if they do something wrong.]
Having a soft or tender heart.
Susceptible of pity or other kindly affection; gentle; meek.
Showing great independence or individuality in thought or action
Marked by or expressing individuality; unconventional.
Exhibiting no pretensions, boastfulness, or ostentation; modest.
Not assuming; not bold or forward; not arrogant; modest; not forthputting; retiring.
Having an easygoing, cheerful disposition.
Having a good disposition; naturally mild in temper; easily acquiescent.
Full of or characterized by animation, vigor, or courage.
Animated; full of life; lively; full of spirit or fire.
Requiring others to work hard or meet high expectations.
Showing bravery and willingness to risk danger or criticism.
Bold or courageous; fearless or intrepid; adventurous.
Good at persuading someone to do or believe something.
Openly friendly.
Socially confident.
Friendly and energetic and finding it easy and enjoyable to be with others.
Sincere and serious.
Characterized by or proceeding from an intense and serious state of mind.
Pleasing in manner, behavior, or appearance.
Socially acceptable or adept; amiable; agreeable.
Characterized by kindness; sympathetic.
Having or showing a sympathetic nature.
Having sympathy, compassion, friendliness, and sensitivity to others' emotions.

Having the power to persuade.

Pursuing one's aims and interests forcefully, sometimes unduly so.

Diligent and hard-working.
Constantly, regularly, or habitually active or occupied.
Feeling or showing sympathy and concern for others.

Marked by attentive concern and protectiveness.
Marked by painstaking effort to avoid errors or omissions.

Calling for or requiring great attention.
Capable of changing according to circumstances.
Able to adjust to new conditions.
Appealing to look at.
Pleasing to the senses or mind, as by being beautiful.
Having the power to attract.
Not excited or agitated; composed.
Peaceful, quiet, and without worry.
Peaceful, quiet, or relaxed.

Ready or willing to agree or consent; conformable.
